  "text": "WeText [CITATION_1] starts with a small datasets annotated on character level. It follows two paradigms of bootstrapping: semi-supervised learning and weakly-supervised learning. In the semi-supervised setting, detected character candidates are filtered with a high thresholding value. In the weakly-supervised setting, ground-truth word boxes are used to mask out false positives outside. New instances detected in either way is added to the initial small datasets and re-train the model.",
